employable with helpful insights from those working in specific sectors. The book covers careers in: probation, the police, prisons, the courts, prosecution services and advocacy, youth justice. Packed with hints and tips, advice from current students, useful web links and lists of recommended reading, this book provides a clear guide to the career decision-making and transition processes and covers the essential elements required to making the first step towards securing a job in the above sectors. It will be essential reading for those who want to forge a successful career in any area of the Criminal Justice Sector"--</subfield><subfield code="c">Provided by publisher.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="596"><subfield code="a">16</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Criminal justice, Administration of.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Career development.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1="1" ind2=" " tag="700"><subfield code="a">Rees, Anne,</subfield><subfield code="e">author.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="949"><subfield code="a">HV 7419 R346 2015</subfield><subfield code="c">1</subfield><subfield code="h">UAAU-B</subfield><subfield code="i">0162035223054</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="926"><subfield code="a">HV 7419 R346 2015</subfield><subfield code="w">LC</subfield><subfield code="c">1</subfield><subfield code="i">0162035223054</subfield><subfield code="l">ON_SHELF</subfield><subfield code="m">UAAUG</subfield><subfield code="p">$150.00</subfield><subfield code="r">Y</subfield><subfield code="s">Y</subfield><subfield code="t">BOOK</subfield><subfield code="u">1/14/2015</subfield></datafield></record>